    <header>
        <h1>HTML Coding Examples</h1>
        <p>Learn HTML with interactive examples</p>
    </header>
    
    <div class="container">
        <div class="card">
            <h2>Basic HTML Structure</h2>
            <p>Every HTML document follows a basic structure:</p>
            
            <div class="code-example">
                <span class="tag">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</span><br>
                <span class="tag">&lt;html&gt;</span><br>
                <span class="tag">&lt;head&gt;</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="tag">&lt;title&gt;</span>Page Title<span class="tag">&lt;/title&gt;</span><br>
                <span class="tag">&lt;/head&gt;</span><br>
                <span class="tag">&lt;body&gt;</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="tag">&lt;h1&gt;</span>My First Heading<span class="tag">&lt;/h1&gt;</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="tag">&lt;p&gt;</span>My first paragraph.<span class="tag">&lt;/p&gt;</span><br>
                <span class="tag">&lt;/body&gt;</span><br>
                <span class="tag">&lt;/html&gt;</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
            <h2>Common HTML Elements</h2>
            <p>HTML provides many semantic elements:</p>
            
            <div class="example-output">
                <h3>This is a heading</h3>
                <p>This is a paragraph with <strong>bold text</strong> and <em>italic text</em>.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>List item 1</li>
                    <li>List item 2</li>
                    <li>List item 3</li>
                </ul>
                
                <a href="#">This is a link</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="interactive-demo">
        <h2>Interactive Form Example</h2>
        <p>HTML forms are used to collect user input:</p>
        
        <form id="demoForm">
            <label for="name">Name:</label>
            <input type="text" id="name" placeholder="Enter your name">
            
            <label for="email">Email:</label>
            <input type="email" id="email" placeholder="Enter your email">
            
            <label for="message">Message:</label>
            <textarea id="message" placeholder="Enter your message" rows="4"></textarea>
            
            <button type="submit">Submit Form</button>
        </form>
        <p id="formMessage"></p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="container">
        <div class="card">
            <h2>HTML5 Features</h2>
            <p>HTML5 introduced new semantic elements and APIs:</p>
            
            <div class="code-example">
                <span class="comment">&lt;!-- Semantic elements --&gt;</span><br>
                <span class="tag">&lt;header&gt;</span><span class="tag">&lt;/header&gt;</span><br>
                <span class="tag">&lt;nav&gt;</span><span class="tag">&lt;/nav&gt;</span><br>
                <span class="tag">&lt;section&gt;</span><span class="tag">&lt;/section&gt;</span><br>
                <span class="tag">&lt;article&gt;</span><span class="tag">&lt;/article&gt;</span><br>
                <span class="tag">&lt;footer&gt;</span><span class="tag">&lt;/footer&gt;</span><br>
                <br>
                <span class="comment">&lt;!-- Multimedia --&gt;</span><br>
                <span class="tag">&lt;video</span> <span class="attribute">controls</span><span class="tag">&gt;</span><span class="tag">&lt;/video&gt;</span><br>
                <span class="tag">&lt;audio</span> <span class="attribute">controls</span><span class="tag">&gt;</span><span class="tag">&lt;/audio&gt;</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="card">
            <h2>CSS & JavaScript</h2>
            <p>HTML works with CSS and JavaScript to create interactive web pages:</p>
            
            <div class="code-example">
                <span class="comment">&lt;!-- Linking CSS --&gt;</span><br>
                <span class="tag">&lt;link</span> <span class="attribute">rel=</span><span class="value">"stylesheet"</span> <span class="attribute">href=</span><span class="value">"styles.css"</span><span class="tag">&gt;</span><br>
                <br>
                <span class="comment">&lt;!-- Adding JavaScript --&gt;</span><br>
                <span class="tag">&lt;script </span><span class="attribute">src=</span><span class="value">"script.js"</span><span class="tag">&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</span><br>
                <br>
                <span class="comment">&lt;!-- Inline JavaScript example --&gt;</span><br>
                <span class="tag">&lt;button</span> <span class="attribute">onclick=</span><span class="value">"alert('Hello!')"</span><span class="tag">&gt;</span><br>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;Click me!<br>
                <span class="tag">&lt;/button&gt;</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    
